17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 10-9.5, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 372, O.S.L. 2024 (2 O.S. Supp. 2024,
20 Section 10-9.5), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 10-9.5. A. The State Board of Agriculture shall
22 provide the necessary forms and applications for any person desiring
23 or required to register a poultry feeding operation or expanding
24 operation.
Req. No. 1685 Page 1
1 B. The application to register to operate a new or previously
2 unregistered poultry feeding operation or expanding operation shall
3 contain, at a minimum, the following information:
4 1. Name and address of the owner and operator of the facility;
5 2. Name and address of the poultry feeding operation;
6 3. Number and type of poultry housed or confined;
7 4. Name and address of the integrator whose poultry will be
8 raised by the poultry feeding operation;
9 5. A diagram or map and legal description showing geographical
10 location of the facility on which the perimeters of the facility are
11 designated, location of waters of the state, including, but not
12 limited to, drainage from the facility, poultry waste storage
13 facilities, and land-application sites owned or leased by the
14 applicant or which the applicant has contracted with for the
15 application of poultry waste;
16 6. A copy of the Nutrient Management Plan, or proof of
17 application for such plan, Best Management Practices or any other
18 plans authorized by the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food,
19 and Forestry;
20 7. A copy of:
21 a. a water use permit from the Oklahoma Water Resources
22 Board pursuant to Section 105.9 of Title 82 of the
23 Oklahoma Statutes, or
24
Req. No. 1685 Page 2
1 b. an official statement for water use from the county,
2 municipality, or other political subdivision where the
3 facility resides;
4 8. A statement of ownership.
5 a. If the applicant is a corporation, the name and
6 address of the corporation and the name and address of
7 each officer and registered agent of the corporation
8 shall be included in the application.
9 b. If the applicant is a partnership or other legal
10 entity, the name and address of each partner and
11 stockholder with an ownership interest of ten percent
12 (10%) or more shall be included in the statement.
13 c. The information contained in the statement of
14 ownership shall be public information and shall be
15 available upon request from the State Board of
16 Agriculture;
17
18 8. 9. In order to be considered a resident of this state for
19 purposes of registration, the following shall be made available to
20 the Board:
21 a. for individuals or sole proprietorships applying for
22 registration, proof of state residency for at least
23 three (3) years immediately preceding the date of
24 application. Sufficient documentation of proof of
Req. No. 1685 Page 3
1 residency shall include an unexpired Oklahoma state-
2 issued driver license and a residential property deed
3 to property in this state, or
4 b. for those applicants disclosed in paragraph 8 of this
5 subsection, an affidavit providing proof of residency
6 in this state and legal status for at least three (3)
7 years immediately preceding the date of application;
8 10. The name and address of the person having day-to-day
9 control of the operation, if such person is not the applicant and is
10 acting as agent for the applicant;
11 9. 11. An environmental history from the past three (3) years
12 of any poultry feeding operation established and operated by the
13 applicant or any other operation with common ownership in this state
14 or any other state;
15 10. 12. Environmental awards or citations received or pollution
16 prevention or voluntary remediation efforts undertaken by the
17 applicant; and
18 11. 13. Any other information or records required by the
19 Department for purposes of implementing the Oklahoma Registered
20 Poultry Feeding Operations Act or rules promulgated pursuant
21 thereto.
22 C. In addition to other penalties as may be imposed by law, any
23 person who knowingly makes any false statement, representation, or
24 certification in, omits material data from, or tampers with any
Req. No. 1685 Page 4
1 appl ication for registration shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
2 misdemeanor and may be subject to a fine not more than Ten Thousand
3 Dollars ($10,000.00) for each such violation.
4 D. The owner of a poultry feeding operation shall be
5 responsible for sending written notification to the Department upon
6 changing integrators.
7 E. For a transfer of registration to a new owner, the new owner
8 shall register the operation pursuant to the rules of the
9 Department.
10 F. 1. All operators of poultry feeding operations and poultry
11 waste applicators shall attend educational courses on poultry waste
12 handling. All such operators and applicators shall attend
13 educational training on poultry waste management as provided by
14 Oklahoma State University through the Cooperative Extension Service.
15 All current and new operators and applicators shall receive the
16 initial nine (9) hours of training in the first year and two (2)
17 hours of continuing education every year until the operator or
18 applicator has received a total of nineteen (19) hours of training.
19 Any operator or applicator may attend more hours than is required;
20 however, those hours shall not be carried forward. Upon receiving
21 the nineteen (19) required hours, the operator or applicator shall
22 be required to receive two (2) hours of continuing education every
23 three (3) years. The Cooperative Extension Service shall develop
24 the educational training course to aid in certification. Curricula
Req. No. 1685 Page 5
1 for the training course will include the Cooperative Extension
2 Service waste management facts series and record books or their
3 current equivalent. Courses for poultry waste management shall
4 include the following topics:
5 a. environmental process relevant to protecting water
6 quality in poultry production,
7 b. basic handling systems to manage poultry waste from
8 all types of poultry operations,
9 c. nutrient management, including sampling procedures,
10 application rate determination, equipment calibration,
11 and record-keeping systems,
12 d. relevant laws and rules applicable to poultry waste
13 management in this state, and
14 e. any other related subject as determined by Oklahoma
15 State University in consultation with the Department.
16 2. At the completion of each course, the operator or applicator
17 shall receive a certification verifying completion. The
18 certificates shall be kept on site for five (5) years.
19 3. Failure to obtain the initial nine-hour training and any
20 continuing education as provided in this subsection shall be deemed
21 a violation of the Oklahoma Registered Poultry Feeding Operations
22 Act for operators and the Oklahoma Poultry Waste Applicators
23 Certification Act for applicators.
24
Req. No. 1685 Page 6
1 4. All operators or applicators shall meet the educational
2 requirements of this section no later than December 31 of each year.
3 5. All operators and applicators are solely responsible for
4 obtaining and maintaining all educational requirements established
5 pursuant to the provisions of this subsection.
6 G. No integrator shall enter into any contract with an operator
7 of a poultry feeding operation who is not in compliance with the
8 education requirements of subsection F of this section.
